        <summary>
            Creates an IGraphicsContext instance for the specified window.
            </summary>
        <returns>A new IGraphicsContext instance.</returns>
        <remarks>
          <para>
            The 
            <see cref="M:OpenTK.Platform.Utilities.CreateGraphicsContext(OpenTK.Graphics.GraphicsMode,OpenTK.Platform.IWindowInfo,System.Int32,System.Int32,OpenTK.Graphics.GraphicsContextFlags)" />
            or
            <see cref="M:OpenTK.Platform.Utilities.CreateGraphicsContext(MonoTouch.OpenGLES.EAGLRenderingAPI)" />
            methods must be used before any methods on the 
            the <see cref="T:OpenTK.Graphics.ES11.GL" /> and
            the <see cref="T:OpenTK.Graphics.ES20.GL" /> types can be used.
          </para>
          <block subset="none" type="behaviors">
            Creates a <see cref="T:OpenTK.Graphics.GraphicsContext" /> instance using the 
            <see cref="C:OpenTK.Graphics.GraphicsContext(OpenTK.Graphics.GraphicsMode,OpenTK.Platform.IWindow,System.Int32,System.Int32,OpenTK.Graphics.GraphicsContextFlags)" />
            constructor, then invokes 
            <see cref="M:OpenTK.Graphics.GraphicsContext.MakeCurrent(OpenTK.Platform.IWindowInfo)" />
            with <paramref name="window" />, then calls
            <see cref="M:OpenTK.Graphics.IGraphicsContextInternal.LoadAll" />.
            This results in loading all of the appropriate GL methods, so that
            the <see cref="T:OpenTK.Graphics.ES11.GL" /> and
            the <see cref="T:OpenTK.Graphics.ES20.GL" /> types can be used.
          </block>
        </remarks>
